The paper discusses replication protocols for ensuring high-availability in asynchronous environments with crash failures. This topic falls under the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the similarities and differences between different replication protocols, which is related to the computer networks and communications (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of refinement mappings to understand the correctness of design decisions is related to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The discussion of performance differences between protocols is related to the operating systems (cs.OS) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
